This directory bundles the Statlog (German Credit Data) dataset.

Source:  https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/144 (UCI Machine Learning Repository, dataset #144)
License: CC BY 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
Cite:    UCI Machine Learning Repository, Statlog (German Credit Data), dataset #144.

Redistributed unmodified for the venth `novacredit` demo example. The columns
`target` (1=good/0=bad) and `gender` (male/female) are derived for the fairness
evaluation; see data/german_credit.croissant.json for the field-level provenance.

DISCLOSURE: this same German Credit benchmark backs all three credit demos —
loan-scoring, novacredit and consumer-credit — which share one fairness
measurement (demographic parity on `gender`, seed 42). They illustrate distinct
governance journeys, not three independent systems or three independent
measurements. See venth.yaml (classification.rationale) for the signed disclosure.
